            <div type="edition">
                <ab><lb n="1"/><persName><name key="Petrus">Petr
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>us</name></persName>.</ab></div>
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>Peter.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>old glasses were common in Rome during 3rd-4th century, but due to the style of the
                    artwork, dating the item to the 4th century (or perahps early 5th century) is more probable. Although the
                    provenance of this gold glass is unknown, it probably arrived from the catacombs
                    at Rome. The item is poorly preserved and it is very likely that it bore another inscription for Paulus (cf. NY.NY.MMA.L.11.91.4, NY.NY.MMA.L.16.174.3).</p></div>
            

